1 4. The Bank shall deposit in the higher education infrastructure revolving loan fund all
2 payments of interest and principal paid under loans made from the higher education
3 infrastructure revolving loan fund. The Bank may use a portion of the interest paid on
4 the outstanding loans as a servicing fee to pay for administrative costs which may not
5 exceed one - half of one percent of the amount of the interest payment. All moneys
6 transferred to the fund, interest upon moneys in the fund, and payments to the fund of
7 principal and interest are appropriated to the Bank on a continuing basis for
8 administrative costs and for loan disbursement according to this section.
9 5. The Bank may adopt policies and establish guidelines to administer this loan program
10 in accordance with the provisions of this section and to supplement and leverage the
11 funds in the higher education infrastructure revolving loan fund. Additionally, the Bank
12 may adopt policies allowing participation by local financial institutions.
13 SECTION 2. APPROPRIATION - TRANSFER - HIGHER EDUCATION
14 INFRASTRUCTURE REVOLVING LOAN FUND - ONE-TIME FUNDING. There is appropriated
15 out of any moneys in the general fund in the state treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum
16 of $25,000,000, which the office of management and budget shall transfer to the higher
17 education infrastructure revolving loan fund during the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and
18 ending June 30, 2027. This appropriation is considered a one-time funding item.
